================================================================================
Provenance
================================================================================

chain_c is a C port of the Priscilla BSV chain layer, a TypeScript / scrypt-ts
codebase. The compiled contract artifacts (artifacts/), the Ricardian charter
prose (legal/), and the circom circuit sources (circuits/) originate from that
upstream project and are redistributed here so the repository is self-contained.

================================================================================
Third-party components
================================================================================

This repository vendors the following third-party code under third_party/.
Each retains its own license; the texts are included alongside the sources.

- cJSON (third_party/cJSON/)
  JSON parser/serializer. Copyright (c) 2009-2017 Dave Gamble and cJSON
  contributors. Licensed under the MIT License. See third_party/cJSON/LICENSE.

- Unity (third_party/unity/)
  C unit-test framework. Copyright (c) 2007-2021 Mike Karlesky, Mark VanderVoord,
  Greg Williams. Licensed under the MIT License. See third_party/unity/LICENSE.txt.

- RIPEMD-160 (third_party/ripemd160/)
  Standalone RIPEMD-160 implementation written for this project from the public
  RIPEMD-160 specification (Dobbertin, Bosselaers, Preneel, 1996). Released into
  the public domain. Verified against the canonical RIPEMD-160 test vectors.

- MiMC7 round constants (third_party/mimc7_consts/mimc7_consts.h)
  The 91 MiMC7 round constants are numerical data (keccak-seeded, as specified by
  circomlib) copied verbatim so they are never re-derived at runtime. They are
  reproduced as data for interoperability with the circomlib/scrypt-ts MiMC7 hash.

